<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="redescription">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Redescription of male terminalia</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 23" captionStartId="F23" captionText="Figure 23. Plecia hoffeinsorum, male, terminalia. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.68.60611.figure23" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/501953" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">23</figureCitation>
)
</emphasis>
. Hypopygium width 0.43 mm (N = 1), outline almost rectangular, slightly expanded apicad. Gonostylus 0.22 mm long, attached apically on gonocoxite, long and slender, straight, apically somewhat pointed, with numerous long, curvy setae. Epandrium rather small, rounded-rectangular, posterior edge sligthly convex. Gonocoxosternite apically with a short, blunt tooth on each side just mesal to gonostylus attachment, posterior edge slightly convex.
</paragraph>
